comments:
(Rule, 2011) actually present two possible structures for azurite: \begin{itemize} \item the current structure, with space group $P2_1/c$ \#14, is identical to the structure designated $G7_{4}$ by (Hermann, 1937) except that the OH radical is now separated into the O(IV) and H atom sites, and \item a structure with the same unit cell dimensions but without an inversion site, leading to space group $P2_1$ \#4. \end{itemize} ~ \vspace{-.25in} 
 The difference between the two structures is extremely small, and we choose to use the traditional structure. 
 Structural information was taken from powder diffraction data at 1.28K.
